name: AEDAK Funds
description: Mutual funds offered by EFG Eurobank and Deutsche Bank

name: Euronext - Growth Amsterdam
description: The Euronext is a pan-European bourse providing trading services. This is the Euronext Growth market operating in Amsterdam, Netherlands. Euronext Growth is suited to small and mid sized companies (SMEs).  Investors can trade here stocks, bonds, stock options, index options and index futures.

name: Euronext - Growth Brussels
description: The Euronext is a pan-European bourse providing trading services. This is the Euronext Growth market operating in Brussels. Euronext Growth is suited to small and mid sized companies (SMEs). Investors can trade here stocks, bonds and index funds.

name: Euronext - Growth Paris
description: The Euronext is a pan-European bourse providing trading services. This is the Euronext Growth market operating in Paris, France. Euronext Growth is suited to small and mid sized companies (SMEs).  Investors can trade here stocks, bonds, ETFs, options, futures, commodities, warrants and other securities

name: Finesti S.A.
description: Finesti is a Luxembourg-based company for managing of data related to investment funds. It was founded in 1995 and it is part of the Luxembourg Stock Exchange.

name: Athens Stock Exchange Alternative Market
description: The Athens Stock Exchange (ASE or ATHEX) is the stock exchange of Greece, based in the capital city of Athens. It was founded in 1876. This is a secondary market, addressed to SMEs and early-stage business development companies.

name: Euronext Access Lisbon
description: The Euronext is a pan-European bourse providing trading services. This is the Euronext Access market operating in Lisbon, Portugal. Euronext Growth is suited to start-ups and SMEs.  Investors can trade here stocks, bonds, ETFs and warrants.

name: Electronic Secondary Securities Market
description: The Electronic Secondary Securities Market (HDAT) is  a secondary market operated by the Bank of Greece. It was founded in 1999. Investors can trade Greek governement securities, bonds, fixed-income debt securities.

name: Borsa Italiana
description: Borsa Italiana is the Italian Stock Exchange, based in Milan. It is expected to be rebranded as Euronext Milan. It was founded in 1808. Investors can trade stocks, ETPs, funds, derivatives and bonds.

name: Other OTC
description: Securities in this market are sold by their owner. These are stocks, bonds and other financial securities which are traded directly between two parties, instead of on a public stock market.

name: MTS Portugal
description: MTS Portugal was a regulated market for trading of Portuguese government securities. MTS is no longer trading since the end of 2019.

name: Euronext - Euronext Amsterdam
description: The Euronext is a pan-European bourse providing trading services. This is the Euronext market operating in Amsterdam, Netherlands. Investors can trade here stocks, bonds, stock options, index options and index futures.

name: Irish Stock Exchange Global Exchange Market
description: The Irish Stock Exchange (also known as Euronext Dublin) is Ireland's main stock exchange, based in Dublin. It was founded in 1793. Investors can trade stocks, bonds, Irish government onds, funds and ETFs.

name: Australia Securities Exchange All Markets
description: The Australian Securities Exchange is the primary securities exchange in Australia. Investors can trade equities, fixed income, commodities and energy.

name: Athens Exchange S.A. Cash Market
description: The Athens Stock Exchange (ASE or ATHEX) is the stock exchange of Greece, based in the capital city of Athens. It was founded in 1876. This is the main trading market, known as the regulated securities market. Here investors can trade in stocks, bonds, ETFs and other related securities.

name: Borsa de Barcelona
description: Borsa de Barcelona is a Spanish stock exchange, based in Barcelona. It was founded in 1915. It is exclusively dedicated to the trade of shares and convertible values.

name: Boerse Berlin
description: The Boerse Berlin (or Berlin Stock Exchange) is a stock exchange based in Berlin, Germany. It was founded in 1685. Investors can trade stocks and bonds.

name: The International Stock Exchange
description: The Internationa Stock Exchange (TISE) is a stock exchange based in St. Peter Port, Guernsey. It was founded in 2013. Investors can trade equities and bonds

name: Cyprus Stock Exchange
description: The Cyprus Stock Exchange (CSE) is the stock exchange of Cyprus, based in Nicosia. It was founded in 1996. Investors can trade shares and bonds.

name: Irish Stock Exchange All Markets
description: The Irish Stock Exchange (also known as Euronext Dublin) is Ireland's main stock exchange, based in Dublin. It was founded in 1793. Investors can trade stocks, bonds, Irish government onds, funds and ETFs.

name: Xetra
description: Xetra is a trading venue operated by the Frankfurt Stock Exchange. It is the reference market for German equities and ETFs.

name: NASDAQ Helsinki Limited
description: NASDAQ Helsinki is a stock exchange located in Helsinki, Finland. It was founded in 1912. Investors can trade stocks.

name: Hong Kong Exchanges and Clearing Ltd
description: Hong Kong Exchanges and Clearing Limited  operates a range of equity, commoditiy, fixed income and currency markets. It was founded in 2000.

name: London Stock Exchange
description: The London Stock Exchange (LSE) is a stock exchange based in the City of London, England. It was founded in 1801 and it is the most-valued stock exchange in Europe. Investors can trade stocks, bonds and ETFs.

name: Luxembourg Stock Exchange
description: The Luxembourg Stock Exchange is a stock exchange based in Luxembourgh City. It was founded in 1928. It primarily specializes in the listing of international bonds.

name: Bolsa de Madrid
description: Bolsa de Madrid is the largest and most international of Spanish stock exchanges. It was founded in 1831. Investors can trade shares, convertible bonds and fixed income securities, as well as both government and private-sector debt. It is owned by Bolsas y Mercados Espanoles (BME)

name: The Montreal Exchange / Bourse de Montreal
description: The Montreal Exchange is a derivatives exchange located in Montreal, Canada. It was founded in 1965. Investors can trade futures contracts and options on equities, indices, currencies, ETFs, energy and interest rates.

name: Boerse Muenchen
description: The Börse München is a stock exchange based in Munich, Germany. It was founded in 1830. In this market, investors can trade in stocks, bonds, funds, ETFs and derivatives.

name: NASDAQ All Markets
description: NASDAQ (National Association of Securities Dealears Automated Quotations) is an American stock exchange based in New York. It is the most active stock trading venue in the USA by volume. It was founded in 1971. Investors can trade stocks, options, ETfs, mutual funds, commodities, cryptocurrencies or futures, among other securities.

name: National Stock Exchange of Australia Limited
description: The National Stock Exchange of Australia is a stock exchange based in Sidney. It was founded in 1937. Investors can exchange equities, debt and managed investment schemes.

name: NASDAQ/NGS (Global Select Market)
description: NASDAQ (National Association of Securities Dealears Automated Quotations) is an American stock exchange based in New York. It is the most active stock trading venue in the USA by volume. It was founded in 1971. This market is the Global Select Market,which has the highest initial listing standards. Investors can trade stocks, options, ETfs, mutual funds, commodities, cryptocurrencies or futures, among other securities.

name: NASDAQ/NMS (Global Market)
description: NASDAQ (National Association of Securities Dealears Automated Quotations) is an American stock exchange based in New York. It is the most active stock trading venue in the USA by volume. It was founded in 1971. This market is the Global Market,the second U.S. market tier, listing companies with global leadership and international reach. Investors can trade stocks, options, ETfs, mutual funds, commodities, cryptocurrencies or futures, among other securities.

name: New York Stock Exchange
description: The New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) is an American stock exchange. It was founded in 1792 and it is the largest stock exchange worldwide. Investors can trade stocks, bonds, options and ETPs.

name: Oslo Bors
description: The Oslo Bors (or Oslo Stock Exchange) is the only regulated market in Norway, based in Oslo. It was founded in 1819. Investors can trade equities, derivatives and fixed income instruments.

name: Euronext - Euronext Paris
description: The Euronext is a pan-European bourse providing trading services. This is the Euronext market operating in Paris, France. Investors can trade here stocks, bonds, ETFs, options, futures, commodities, warrants and other securities

name: Boerse Stuttgart
description: Boerse Stuttgart (SWB) is the second largest stock exchange in Germany, based in Stuttgart. It was founded in 1860. Investors can trade stocks, bonds, warrants, ETPs, funds, etc.

name: SIX Swiss Exchange
description: The SIX Swiss Exchange is Switzerland's principal stock exchange. It was founded in its current form in 1993. Investors can trade stocks, Swiss government bonds and derivatives.

name: Electronic Book Building Athex
description: The EBB (Electronic Book Building)  is a service offered by ATHEX to support fund-raising process through ATHEX. It is a mechanism provided centrally in the trading order routing system, in an attempt to use the network of ATHEX members and their clients.
